{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"8e06776c-fc50-4d22-84e2-108b2b2f587f","content":"In ASP.NET Core, `AddScoped` creates a new instance **per HTTP request** — each request is a natural scope boundary. In MAUI, **there is no equivalent automatic scope**. The app has a single long-lived scope, so `AddScoped` effectively behaves like `AddSingleton` — your DbContext lives for the entire app session.\n\n**Fixes:**\n\n1. **Use `AddTransient`** — gives a fresh DbContext each time it's injected.\n2. **Use `IServiceScopeFactory`** to manually create and dispose scopes:\n\n```csharp\npublic class MyViewModel\n{\n    private readonly IServiceScopeFactory _scopeFactory;\n\n    public MyViewModel(IServiceScopeFactory scopeFactory)\n        => _scopeFactory = scopeFactory;\n\n    public async Task LoadData()\n    {\n        using var scope = _scopeFactory.CreateScope();\n        var db = scope.ServiceProvider.GetRequiredService<MyDbContext>();\n        // use db...\n    }\n}\n```\n\nOption 2 is preferred for EF Core since it gives you explicit lifetime control and ensures the context is disposed promptly.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"4447fb68-c137-46b2-8946-d11f0d6ab3f6","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a common pitfall when moving from ASP.NET Core to .NET MAUI regarding dependency injection scopes and DbContext lifetime management.\n\nIn ASP.NET Core, `AddScoped` creates a new instance per HTTP request — each request is a \"scope.\" But in MAUI, there's no concept of an HTTP request. The DI container in MAUI effectively treats `AddScoped` the same as `AddSingleton` because the default scope is the application's lifetime (there's no automatic scope creation per page navigation or per anything else).\n\nThis is a well-known gotcha. I can answer this directly without needing tools.","outputTokens":435,"requestId":"482A:3A5014:55027E6:5D3A204:69F3FD0E"},"id":"cd5e8bfa-bcb9-401c-8f8a-8edc44757e71","timestamp":"2026-05-01T01:08:40.949Z","parentId":"33f9353d-e642-45ec-9b39-62fe37b72295"}
